There we go!

72
00:05:16,941 --> 00:05:18,693
Give us a sample speech.

73
00:05:19,986 --> 00:05:21,612
That's the thing. I don't have any.

74
00:05:21,696 --> 00:05:23,948
There's just so much work at Vertex.

75
00:05:24,032 --> 00:05:26,034
And also here, there's a lot of…

76
00:05:26,617 --> 00:05:27,785
What?

77
00:05:28,453 --> 00:05:30,830
There are a lot of people
who can help write my speech.

78
00:05:31,414 --> 00:05:34,042
You know, I'll lend you my book.

79
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:36,627
The <i>7 Habits of Highly Effective People</i>.

80
00:05:36,711 --> 00:05:39,213
So your speech will be,
you know, inspiring.

81
00:05:39,797 --> 00:05:42,133
And then, I'll refer you to my barber.

82
00:05:42,216 --> 00:05:43,801
Don't worry about me.

83
00:05:43,885 --> 00:05:46,054
And that speech, I can handle that easily.

84
00:05:46,137 --> 00:05:47,889
I'll just take a shot
before going on stage.

85
00:05:47,972 --> 00:05:48,806
That should do it, right?

86
00:05:48,890 --> 00:05:49,849
Just go straight in.

87
00:05:49,932 --> 00:05:51,768
-That's the spirit, Mikoy!
-No need to be nervous.

88
00:05:52,268 --> 00:05:55,104
Looks like you're getting the hang
of being an undercover agent.

89
00:05:56,397 --> 00:05:57,690
Thank you, sir!

90
00:06:01,694 --> 00:06:05,490
But team,
we will be there as undercover agents.

91
00:06:05,573 --> 00:06:09,494
Our goal is to gather
as much intelligence as we can.

92
00:06:10,495 --> 00:06:12,455
With so many elite guests invited there,

93
00:06:12,538 --> 00:06:14,540
